{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idca7bb8b7-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s1768"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1768"},"text":"§ 1768.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Conveyance of lands covered by right-of-way; terms and conditions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"If under applicable law the Secretary concerned decides to transfer out of Federal ownership any lands covered in whole or in part by a right-of-way, including a right-of-way granted under the Act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-11-16"},"text":"November 16, 1973","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/87/576"},"text":"87 Stat. 576","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t30/s185"},"text":"30 U.S.C. 185","children":[],"tail":"), the lands may be conveyed subject to the right-of-way; however, if the Secretary concerned determines that retention of Federal control over the right-of-way is necessary to assure that the purposes of this subchapter will be carried out, the terms and conditions of the right-of-way complied with, or the lands protected, he shall (a) reserve to the United States that portion of the lands which lies within the boundaries of the right-of-way, or (b) convey the lands, including that portion within the boundaries of the right-of-way, subject to the right-of-way and reserving to the United States the right to enforce all or any of the terms and conditions of the right-of-way, including the right to renew it or extend it upon its termination and to collect rents."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idca7bb8b8-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/579/tV/s508"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–579, title V, § 508","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/2781"},"text":"90 Stat. 2781","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idca7bb8b9-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idca7bb8ba-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idca7bb8bb-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-11-16"},"text":"November 16, 1973","children":[],"tail":", referred to in text, is "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/153"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–153","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-11-16"},"text":"Nov. 16, 1973","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/87/576"},"text":"87 Stat. 576","children":[],"tail":". For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"idca7bb8bc-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"idca7bb8bd-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"See note set out under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t43/s1763"},"text":"section 1763 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
